Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and @diced chorizo{60%g} and fry until they start to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Next, add the garlic, stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @water{75%ml} into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @peas{120%g} and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Cook until the peas are piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta. Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste} if needed. Add a splash of @water{?splash} if it's a little too thick.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked through when no longer pink in the middle.

Share the creamy chicken and chorizo linguine between your #bowls{}.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!